-- B&W, Foschini, Gold Fields, Metorex May Move in Early Johannesburg Trading
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 2010-11-16T05:42:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/b-w-foschini-gold-fields-metorex-may-move-in-early-johannesburg-trading.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in South Africa. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close. South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share
Index  climbed 123.81, or 0.4 percent, to 31,816.61 at the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg.  B & W Instrumentation and Electrical Ltd.  (BWI SJ): The
construction group said profit fell 3.4 percent to 57.3 million
rand in the year through August. The stock fell 3 cents, or 2
percent, to 1.47 rand.  Foschini Ltd.  (TFG SJ): The South African clothing retailer
will release first-half earnings. The stock gained 2.39 rand, or
2.8 percent, to 89.39 rand.  Gold Fields Ltd.  (GFI SJ): Africa’s second-largest producer
of the precious metal, faces another day of strikes at its South
Deep Mine, after workers downed tools on Nov. 12 in support of
their demand for the company to employ more black managers. Gold
Fields retreated 1.90 rand, or 1.5 percent, to 121.66 rand.  Lonmin Plc  (LON SJ): The world’s third-largest platinum
producer meets with analysts following its annual results
yesterday. The company surged 9 rand, or 4.6 percent, to 206
rand. Anglo Platinum Ltd. (AMS SJ), the largest producer,
climbed 6.45 rand, or 0.9 percent, to 708.80 rand.  Metorex Ltd.  (MTX SJ): The cobalt and copper producer said
output at its Ruashi mine in the Democratic Republic of Congo
has been curbed by recurring electrical faults and is operating
at reduced throughput of 50 percent. Metorex declined 6 cents,
or 1.2 percent, to 4.83 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of South African
companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) gained 0.1 percent to $24.14.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) dropped 0.8 percent to $48.69.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) rose 0.2 percent to $4.97. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) decreased 0.9 percent to $17.16. Harmony Gold
Mining Co. (HMY US) fell 1.4 percent to $12.01. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) climbed 2.2 percent to $30.85. Sappi Ltd.
(SPP US) declined 0.5 percent to $5.59. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose
0.4 percent to $48.16.  To contact the reporter on this story:
